  <Name>k__BackingField: Zechariah
  fancyName: 
  nickname: zec
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: bd3f8ba6a2445b646991a3e44f7f687a, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  In the eighth month, in the second year of Darius, came the word
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> unto Zechariah, the son of Berechiah,
        the son of Iddo the prophet, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: Call to Repentance'
      title: Call to Repentance
      number: 2
      content: 'The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> hath been sore displeased with your
        fathers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore say thou unto them, Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        of hosts; Turn ye unto me, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts,
        and I will turn unto you, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Be ye not as your fathers, unto whom the former prophets have cried,
        saying, Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts; Turn ye now
        from your evil ways, and <i>from</i> your evil doings: but they did not hear,
        nor hearken unto me, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Your fathers, where <i>are</i> they? and the prophets, do they live
        for ever? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Visions of the NightAmong the Myrtle Trees'
      title: Visions of the NightAmong the Myrtle Trees
      number: 6
      content: 'But my words and my statutes, which I commanded my servants the prophets,
        did they not take hold of your fathers? and they returned and said, Like
        as the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts thought to do unto us, according
        to our ways, and according to our doings, so hath he dealt with us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Upon the four and twentieth day of the eleventh month, which <i>is</i>
        the month Sebat, in the second year of Darius, came the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        unto Zechariah, the son of Berechiah, the son of Iddo the prophet, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I saw by night, and behold a man riding upon a red horse, and he
        stood among the myrtle trees that <i>were</i> in the bottom; and behind him
        <i>were there</i> red horses, speckled, and white. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then said I, O my lord, what <i>are</i> these? And the angel that
        talked with me said unto me, I will shew thee what these <i>be</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the man that stood among the myrtle trees answered and said,
        These <i>are they</i> whom the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> hath sent to walk
        to and fro through the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And they answered the angel of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> that
        stood among the myrtle trees, and said, We have walked to and fro through
        the earth, and, behold, all the earth sitteth still, and is at rest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then the angel of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> answered and said,
        O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts, how long wilt thou not have mercy
        on Jerusalem and on the cities of Judah, against which thou hast had indignation
        these threescore and ten years? '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> answered the angel that talked
        with me <i>with</i> good words <i>and</i> comfortable words. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So the angel that communed with me said unto me, Cry thou, saying,
        Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts; I am jealous for Jerusalem
        and for Zion with a great jealousy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And I am very sore displeased with the heathen <i>that are</i> at
        ease: for I was but a little displeased, and they helped forward the affliction. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Therefore thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>; I am returned
        to Jerusalem with mercies: my house shall be built in it, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        of hosts, and a line shall be stretched forth upon Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Four Horns'
      title: Four Horns
      number: 17
      content: 'Cry yet, saying, Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts;
        My cities through prosperity shall yet be spread abroad; and the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        shall yet comfort Zion, and shall yet choose Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then lifted I up mine eyes, and saw, and behold four horns. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And I said unto the angel that talked with me, What <i>be</i> these?
        And he answered me, These <i>are</i> the horns which have scattered Judah,
        Israel, and Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> shewed me four carpenters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then said I, What come these to do? And he spake, saying, These <i>are</i>
        the horns which have scattered Judah, so that no man did lift up his head:
        but these are come to fray them, to cast out the horns of the Gentiles, which
        lifted up <i>their</i> horn over the land of Judah to scatter it.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Measuring Line'
      title: A Measuring Line
      number: 1
      content: '  I lifted up mine eyes again, and looked, and behold a man with
        a measuring line in his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then said I, Whither goest thou? And he said unto me, To measure
        Jerusalem, to see what <i>is</i> the breadth thereof, and what <i>is</i>
        the length thereof. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And, behold, the angel that talked with me went forth, and another
        angel went out to meet him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and said unto him, Run, speak to this young man, saying, Jerusalem
        shall be inhabited <i>as</i> towns without walls for the multitude of men
        and cattle therein: '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For I, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, will be unto her a
        wall of fire round about, and will be the glory in the midst of her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Ho, ho, <i>come forth</i>, and flee from the land of the north, saith
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>: for I have spread you abroad as the four
        winds of the heaven, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Deliver thyself, O Zion, that dwellest <i>with</i> the daughter of
        Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts; After the
        glory hath he sent me unto the nations which spoiled you: for he that toucheth
        you toucheth the apple of his eye. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For, behold, I will shake mine hand upon them, and they shall be
        a spoil to their servants: and ye shall know that the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        of hosts hath sent me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Sing and rejoice, O daughter of Zion: for, lo, I come, and I will
        dwell in the midst of thee, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And many nations shall be joined to the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        in that day, and shall be my people: and I will dwell in the midst of thee,
        and thou shalt know that the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts hath sent
        me unto thee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> shall inherit Judah his portion
        in the holy land, and shall choose Jerusalem again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Be silent, O all flesh, before the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>: for
        he is raised up out of his holy habitation.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Trial of the High Priest'
      title: The Trial of the High Priest
      number: 1
      content: '  And he shewed me Joshua the high priest standing before the angel
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and Satan standing at his right hand
        to resist him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> said unto Satan, The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        rebuke thee, O Satan; even the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> that hath chosen
        Jerusalem rebuke thee: <i>is</i> not this a brand plucked out of the fire? '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now Joshua was clothed with filthy garments, and stood before the
        angel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And he answered and spake unto those that stood before him, saying,
        Take away the filthy garments from him. And unto him he said, Behold, I have
        caused thine iniquity to pass from thee, and I will clothe thee with change
        of raiment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And I said, Let them set a fair mitre upon his head. So they set
        a fair mitre upon his head, and clothed him with garments. And the angel
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> stood by.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the angel of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> protested unto Joshua,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts; If thou wilt
        walk in my ways, and if thou wilt keep my charge, then thou shalt also judge
        my house, and shalt also keep my courts, and I will give thee places to walk
        among these that stand by. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Hear now, O Joshua the high priest, thou, and thy fellows that sit
        before thee: for they <i>are</i> men wondered at: for, behold, I will bring
        forth my servant the BRANCH. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For behold the stone that I have laid before Joshua; upon one stone
        <i>shall be</i> seven eyes: behold, I will engrave the graving thereof, saith
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts, and I will remove the iniquity
        of that land in one day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: In that day, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts, shall
        ye call every man his neighbour under the vine and under the fig tree.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Golden Candlestick'
      title: A Golden Candlestick
      number: 1
      content: '  And the angel that talked with me came again, and waked me, as
        a man that is wakened out of his sleep, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and said unto me, What seest thou? And I said, I have looked, and
        behold a candlestick all <i>of</i> gold, with a bowl upon the top of it,
        and his seven lamps thereon, and seven pipes to the seven lamps, which <i>are</i>
        upon the top thereof: '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and two olive trees by it, one upon the right <i>side</i> of the
        bowl, and the other upon the left <i>side</i> thereof.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So I answered and spake to the angel that talked with me, saying,
        What <i>are</i> these, my lord? '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the angel that talked with me answered and said unto me, Knowest
        thou not what these be? And I said, No, my lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then he answered and spake unto me, saying, This <i>is</i> the word
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> unto Zerubbabel, saying, Not by might,
        nor by power, but by my spirit, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of
        hosts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Who <i>art</i> thou, O great mountain? before Zerubbabel <i>thou
        shalt become</i> a plain: and he shall bring forth the headstone <i>thereof
        with</i> shoutings, <i>crying</i>, Grace, grace unto it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Moreover the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> came unto me,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The hands of Zerubbabel have laid the foundation of this house; his
        hands shall also finish it; and thou shalt know that the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        of hosts hath sent me unto you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For who hath despised the day of small things? for they shall rejoice,
        and shall see the plummet in the hand of Zerubbabel <i>with</i> those seven;
        they <i>are</i> the eyes of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, which run to
        and fro through the whole earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then answered I, and said unto him, What <i>are</i> these two olive
        trees upon the right <i>side</i> of the candlestick and upon the left <i>side</i>
        thereof? '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And I answered again, and said unto him, What <i>be these</i> two
        olive branches which through the two golden pipes empty the golden <i>oil</i>
        out of themselves? '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And he answered me and said, Knowest thou not what these <i>be?</i>
        And I said, No, my lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Then said he, These <i>are</i> the two anointed ones, that stand by
        the Lord of the whole earth.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Flying Roll'
      title: A Flying Roll
      number: 1
      content: '  Then I turned, and lifted up mine eyes, and looked, and behold
        a flying roll. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he said unto me, What seest thou? And I answered, I see a flying
        roll; the length thereof <i>is</i> twenty cubits, and the breadth thereof
        ten cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then said he unto me, This <i>is</i> the curse that goeth forth over
        the face of the whole earth: for every one that stealeth shall be cut off
        <i>as</i> on this side according to it; and every one that sweareth shall
        be cut off <i>as</i> on that side according to it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: An Ephah and a Talent'
      title: An Ephah and a Talent
      number: 4
      content: 'I will bring it forth, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts,
        and it shall enter into the house of the thief, and into the house of him
        that sweareth falsely by my name: and it shall remain in the midst of his
        house, and shall consume it with the timber thereof and the stones thereof.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the angel that talked with me went forth, and said unto me,
        Lift up now thine eyes, and see what <i>is</i> this that goeth forth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And I said, What <i>is</i> it? And he said, This <i>is</i> an ephah
        that goeth forth. He said moreover, This <i>is</i> their resemblance through
        all the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And, behold, there was lifted up a talent of lead: and this <i>is</i>
        a woman that sitteth in the midst of the ephah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And he said, This <i>is</i> wickedness. And he cast it into the midst
        of the ephah; and he cast the weight of lead upon the mouth thereof. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then lifted I up mine eyes, and looked, and, behold, there came out
        two women, and the wind <i>was</i> in their wings; for they had wings like
        the wings of a stork: and they lifted up the ephah between the earth and
        the heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then said I to the angel that talked with me, Whither do these bear
        the ephah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And he said unto me, To build it an house in the land of Shinar:
        and it shall be established, and set there upon her own base.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Four Chariots'
      title: Four Chariots
      number: 1
      content: '  And I turned, and lifted up mine eyes, and looked, and, behold,
        there came four chariots out from between two mountains; and the mountains
        <i>were</i> mountains of brass. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'In the first chariot <i>were</i> red horses; and in the second chariot
        black horses; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and in the third chariot white horses; and in the fourth chariot
        grisled and bay horses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then I answered and said unto the angel that talked with me, What
        <i>are</i> these, my lord? '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the angel answered and said unto me, These <i>are</i> the four
        spirits of the heavens, which go forth from standing before the Lord of all
        the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The black horses which <i>are</i> therein go forth into the north
        country; and the white go forth after them; and the grisled go forth toward
        the south country. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the bay went forth, and sought to go that they might walk to
        and fro through the earth: and he said, Get you hence, walk to and fro through
        the earth. So they walked to and fro through the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The New JerusalemA Coronation'
      title: The New JerusalemA Coronation
      number: 8
      content: 'Then cried he upon me, and spake unto me, saying, Behold, these that
        go toward the north country have quieted my spirit in the north country.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> came unto me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Take of <i>them of</i> the captivity, <i>even</i> of Heldai, of Tobijah,
        and of Jedaiah, which are come from Babylon, and come thou the same day,
        and go into the house of Josiah the son of Zephaniah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'then take silver and gold, and make crowns, and set <i>them</i> upon
        the head of Joshua the son of Josedech, the high priest; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and speak unto him, saying, Thus speaketh the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        of hosts, saying, Behold the man whose name <i>is</i> The BRANCH; and he
        shall grow up out of his place, and he shall build the temple of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'even he shall build the temple of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>;
        and he shall bear the glory, and shall sit and rule upon his throne; and
        he shall be a priest upon his throne: and the counsel of peace shall be between
        them both. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And the crowns shall be to Helem, and to Tobijah, and to Jedaiah,
        and to Hen the son of Zephaniah, for a memorial in the temple of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: And they <i>that are</i> far off shall come and build in the temple
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and ye shall know that the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        of hosts hath sent me unto you. And <i>this</i> shall come to pass, if ye
        will diligently obey the voice of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> your God.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: True Righteousness'
      title: True Righteousness
      number: 1
      content: '  And it came to pass in the fourth year of king Darius, <i>that</i>
        the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> came unto Zechariah in the fourth
        <i>day</i> of the ninth month, <i>even</i> in Chisleu; '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'when they had sent unto the house of God Sherezer and Regem-melech,
        and their men, to pray before the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '<i>and</i> to speak unto the priests which <i>were</i> in the house
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts, and to the prophets, saying,
        Should I weep in the fifth month, separating myself, as I have done these
        so many years? '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then came the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts unto
        me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Speak unto all the people of the land, and to the priests, saying,
        When ye fasted and mourned in the fifth and seventh <i>month</i>, even those
        seventy years, did ye at all fast unto me, <i>even</i> to me? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And when ye did eat, and when ye did drink, did not ye eat <i>for
        yourselves</i>, and drink <i>for yourselves?</i>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '<i>Should ye</i> not <i>hear</i> the words which the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        hath cried by the former prophets, when Jerusalem was inhabited and in prosperity,
        and the cities thereof round about her, when <i>men</i> inhabited the south
        and the plain?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> came unto Zechariah,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Thus speaketh the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts, saying, Execute
        true judgment, and shew mercy and compassions every man to his brother: '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and oppress not the widow, nor the fatherless, the stranger, nor
        the poor; and let none of you imagine evil against his brother in your heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But they refused to hearken, and pulled away the shoulder, and stopped
        their ears, that they should not hear. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Yea, they made their hearts <i>as</i> an adamant stone, lest they
        should hear the law, and the words which the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        of hosts hath sent in his spirit by the former prophets: therefore came a
        great wrath from the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Therefore it is come to pass, <i>that</i> as he cried, and they would
        not hear; so they cried, and I would not hear, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        of hosts: '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'but I scattered them with a whirlwind among all the nations whom
        they knew not. Thus the land was desolate after them, that no man passed
        through nor returned: for they laid the pleasant land desolate.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A City of Truth'
      title: A City of Truth
      number: 1
      content: '  Again the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts came
        <i>to me</i>, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts; I was jealous
        for Zion with great jealousy, and I was jealous for her with great fury. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>; I am returned unto Zion,
        and will dwell in the midst of Jerusalem: and Jerusalem shall be called a
        city of truth; and the mountain of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts
        the holy mountain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts; There shall
        yet old men and old women dwell in the streets of Jerusalem, and every man
        with his staff in his hand for very age. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the streets of the city shall be full of boys and girls playing
        in the streets thereof. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts; If it be marvellous
        in the eyes of the remnant of this people in these days, should it also be
        marvellous in mine eyes? saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts; Behold, I will
        save my people from the east country, and from the west country; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and I will bring them, and they shall dwell in the midst of Jerusalem:
        and they shall be my people, and I will be their God, in truth and in righteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts; Let your hands
        be strong, ye that hear in these days these words by the mouth of the prophets,
        which <i>were</i> in the day <i>that</i> the foundation of the house of the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts was laid, that the temple might be built. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For before these days there was no hire for man, nor any hire for
        beast; neither <i>was there any</i> peace to him that went out or came in
        because of the affliction: for I set all men every one against his neighbour. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But now I <i>will</i> not <i>be</i> unto the residue of this people
        as in the former days, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For the seed <i>shall be</i> prosperous; the vine shall give her
        fruit, and the ground shall give her increase, and the heavens shall give
        their dew; and I will cause the remnant of this people to possess all these
        <i>things</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And it shall come to pass, <i>that</i> as ye were a curse among the
        heathen, O house of Judah, and house of Israel; so will I save you, and ye
        shall be a blessing: fear not, <i>but</i> let your hands be strong.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts; As I thought
        to punish you, when your fathers provoked me to wrath, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        of hosts, and I repented not: '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'so again have I thought in these days to do well unto Jerusalem and
        to the house of Judah: fear ye not. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'These <i>are</i> the things that ye shall do; Speak ye every man
        the truth to his neighbour; execute the judgment of truth and peace in your
        gates: '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'and let none of you imagine evil in your hearts against his neighbour;
        and love no false oath: for all these <i>are things</i> that I hate, saith
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts came unto
        me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts; The fast of
        the fourth <i>month</i>, and the fast of the fifth, and the fast of the seventh,
        and the fast of the tenth, shall be to the house of Judah joy and gladness,
        and cheerful feasts; therefore love the truth and peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts; <i>It shall</i>
        yet <i>come to pass</i>, that there shall come people, and the inhabitants
        of many cities: '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'and the inhabitants of one <i>city</i> shall go to another, saying,
        Let us go speedily to pray before the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and to
        seek the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts: I will go also. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Yea, many people and strong nations shall come to seek the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        of hosts in Jerusalem, and to pray before the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts; In those days
        <i>it shall come to pass</i>, that ten men shall take hold out of all languages
        of the nations, even shall take hold of the skirt of him that is a Jew, saying,
        We will go with you: for we have heard <i>that</i> God <i>is</i> with you.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The City of GodLook to the Lord'
      title: The City of GodLook to the Lord
      number: 1
      content: '  The burden of the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> in the
        land of Hadrach, and Damascus <i>shall be</i> the rest thereof: when the
        eyes of man, as of all the tribes of Israel, <i>shall be</i> toward the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Hamath also shall border thereby; Tyrus, and Zidon, though it
        be very wise. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Tyrus did build herself a strong hold, and heaped up silver as
        the dust, and fine gold as the mire of the streets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Behold, the Lord will cast her out, and he will smite her power in
        the sea; and she shall be devoured with fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Ashkelon shall see <i>it</i>, and fear; Gaza also <i>shall see it</i>,
        and be very sorrowful, and Ekron; for her expectation shall be ashamed; and
        the king shall perish from Gaza, and Ashkelon shall not be inhabited. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And a bastard shall dwell in Ashdod, and I will cut off the pride
        of the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And I will take away his blood out of his mouth, and his abominations
        from between his teeth: but he that remaineth, even he, <i>shall be</i> for
        our God, and he shall be as a governor in Judah, and Ekron as a Jebusite.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The King of Peace'
      title: The King of Peace
      number: 8
      content: 'And I will encamp about mine house because of the army, because of
        him that passeth by, and because of him that returneth: and no oppressor
        shall pass through them any more: for now have I seen with mine eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Rejoice greatly, O daughter of Zion; shout, O daughter of Jerusalem:
        behold, thy King cometh unto thee: he <i>is</i> just, and having salvation;
        lowly, and riding upon an ass, and upon a colt the foal of an ass. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And I will cut off the chariot from Ephraim, and the horse from Jerusalem,
        and the battle bow shall be cut off: and he shall speak peace unto the heathen:
        and his dominion <i>shall be</i> from sea <i>even</i> to sea, and from the
        river <i>even</i> to the ends of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'As for thee also, by the blood of thy covenant I have sent forth
        thy prisoners out of the pit wherein <i>is</i> no water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Turn you to the strong hold, ye prisoners of hope: even to day do
        I declare <i>that</i> I will render double unto thee; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'when I have bent Judah for me, filled the bow with Ephraim, and raised
        up thy sons, O Zion, against thy sons, O Greece, and made thee as the sword
        of a mighty man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: He Will Save His People'
      title: He Will Save His People
      number: 14
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> shall be seen over them, and
        his arrow shall go forth as the lightning: and the Lord <smallcaps>GOD</smallcaps>
        shall blow the trumpet, and shall go with whirlwinds of the south.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts shall defend them; and they
        shall devour, and subdue with sling stones; and they shall drink, <i>and</i>
        make a noise as through wine; and they shall be filled like bowls, <i>and</i>
        as the corners of the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> their God shall save them in
        that day as the flock of his people: for <i>they shall be as</i> the stones
        of a crown, lifted up as an ensign upon his land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: For how great <i>is</i> his goodness, and how great <i>is</i> his
        beauty! corn shall make the young men cheerful, and new wine the maids.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  Ask ye of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> rain in the time of the
        latter rain; <i>so</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> shall make bright
        clouds, and give them showers of rain, to every one grass in the field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For the idols have spoken vanity, and the diviners have seen a lie,
        and have told false dreams; they comfort in vain: therefore they went their
        way as a flock, they were troubled, because <i>there was</i> no shepherd.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Mine anger was kindled against the shepherds, and I punished the
        goats: for the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts hath visited his flock
        the house of Judah, and hath made them as his goodly horse in the battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Out of him came forth the corner, out of him the nail, out of him
        the battle bow, out of him every oppressor together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Judah and Israel'
      title: Judah and Israel
      number: 5
      content: 'And they shall be as mighty <i>men</i>, which tread down <i>their
        enemies</i> in the mire of the streets in the battle: and they shall fight,
        because the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>  <i>is</i> with them, and the riders
        on horses shall be confounded.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And I will strengthen the house of Judah, and I will save the house
        of Joseph, and I will bring them again to place them; for I have mercy upon
        them: and they shall be as though I had not cast them off: for I <i>am</i>
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> their God, and will hear them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And <i>they of</i> Ephraim shall be like a mighty <i>man</i>, and
        their heart shall rejoice as through wine: yea, their children shall see
        <i>it</i>, and be glad; their heart shall rejoice in the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I will hiss for them, and gather them; for I have redeemed them:
        and they shall increase as they have increased. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And I will sow them among the people: and they shall remember me
        in far countries; and they shall live with their children, and turn again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I will bring them again also out of the land of Egypt, and gather
        them out of Assyria; and I will bring them into the land of Gilead and Lebanon;
        and <i>place</i> shall not be found for them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And he shall pass through the sea with affliction, and shall smite
        the waves in the sea, and all the deeps of the river shall dry up: and the
        pride of Assyria shall be brought down, and the sceptre of Egypt shall depart
        away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: And I will strengthen them in the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>; and
        they shall walk up and down in his name, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Their Glory is Spoiled'
      title: Their Glory is Spoiled
      number: 1
      content: '  Open thy doors, O Lebanon, that the fire may devour thy cedars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Howl, fir tree; for the cedar is fallen; because the mighty are spoiled:
        howl, O ye oaks of Bashan; for the forest of the vintage is come down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '<i>There is</i> a voice of the howling of the shepherds; for their
        glory is spoiled: a voice of the roaring of young lions; for the pride of
        Jordan is spoiled.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> my God; Feed the flock
        of the slaughter; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'whose possessors slay them, and hold themselves not guilty: and they
        that sell them say, Blessed <i>be</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>; for
        I am rich: and their own shepherds pity them not. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For I will no more pity the inhabitants of the land, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>:
        but, lo, I will deliver the men every one into his neighbour''s hand, and
        into the hand of his king: and they shall smite the land, and out of their
        hand I will not deliver <i>them</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And I will feed the flock of slaughter, <i>even</i> you, O poor of
        the flock. And I took unto me two staves; the one I called Beauty, and the
        other I called Bands; and I fed the flock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Three shepherds also I cut off in one month; and my soul lothed them,
        and their soul also abhorred me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then said I, I will not feed you: that that dieth, let it die; and
        that that is to be cut off, let it be cut off; and let the rest eat every
        one the flesh of another.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And I took my staff, <i>even</i> Beauty, and cut it asunder, that
        I might break my covenant which I had made with all the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And it was broken in that day: and so the poor of the flock that
        waited upon me knew that it <i>was</i> the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And I said unto them, If ye think good, give <i>me</i> my price;
        and if not, forbear. So they weighed for my price thirty <i>pieces</i> of
        silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> said unto me, Cast it unto the
        potter: a goodly price that I was prised at of them. And I took the thirty
        <i>pieces</i> of silver, and cast them to the potter in the house of the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then I cut asunder mine other staff, <i>even</i> Bands, that I might
        break the brotherhood between Judah and Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> said unto me, Take unto thee
        yet the instruments of a foolish shepherd. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For, lo, I will raise up a shepherd in the land, <i>which</i> shall
        not visit those that be cut off, neither shall seek the young one, nor heal
        that that is broken, nor feed that that standeth still: but he shall eat
        the flesh of the fat, and tear their claws in pieces. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Woe to the idol shepherd that leaveth the flock! the sword <i>shall
        be</i> upon his arm, and upon his right eye: his arm shall be clean dried
        up, and his right eye shall be utterly darkened.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Trembling City'
      title: A Trembling City
      number: 1
      content: '  The burden of the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> for Israel,
        saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, which stretcheth forth the heavens,
        and layeth the foundation of the earth, and formeth the spirit of man within
        him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Behold, I will make Jerusalem a cup of trembling unto all the people
        round about, when they shall be in the siege both against Judah <i>and</i>
        against Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And in that day will I make Jerusalem a burdensome stone for all
        people: all that burden themselves with it shall be cut in pieces, though
        all the people of the earth be gathered together against it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'In that day, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, I will smite
        every horse with astonishment, and his rider with madness: and I will open
        mine eyes upon the house of Judah, and will smite every horse of the people
        with blindness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the governors of Judah shall say in their heart, The inhabitants
        of Jerusalem <i>shall be</i> my strength in the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        of hosts their God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'In that day will I make the governors of Judah like an hearth of
        fire among the wood, and like a torch of fire in a sheaf; and they shall
        devour all the people round about, on the right hand and on the left: and
        Jerusalem shall be inhabited again in her own place, <i>even</i> in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> also shall save the tents of Judah
        first, that the glory of the house of David and the glory of the inhabitants
        of Jerusalem do not magnify <i>themselves</i> against Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'In that day shall the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> defend the inhabitants
        of Jerusalem; and he that is feeble among them at that day shall be as David;
        and the house of David <i>shall be</i> as God, as the angel of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        before them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: A Day of Mourning'
      title: A Day of Mourning
      number: 9
      content: 'And it shall come to pass in that day, <i>that</i> I will seek to
        destroy all the nations that come against Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And I will pour upon the house of David, and upon the inhabitants
        of Jerusalem, the spirit of grace and of supplications: and they shall look
        upon me whom they have pierced, and they shall mourn for him, as one mourneth
        for <i>his</i> only <i>son</i>, and shall be in bitterness for him, as one
        that is in bitterness for <i>his</i> firstborn. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'In that day shall there be a great mourning in Jerusalem, as the
        mourning of Hadadrimmon in the valley of Megiddon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the land shall mourn, every family apart; the family of the house
        of David apart, and their wives apart; the family of the house of Nathan
        apart, and their wives apart; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'the family of the house of Levi apart, and their wives apart; the
        family of Shimei apart, and their wives apart; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: all the families that remain, every family apart, and their wives
        apart.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Cleansing Fountain'
      title: A Cleansing Fountain
      number: 1
      content: '  In that day there shall be a fountain opened to the house of David
        and to the inhabitants of Jerusalem for sin and for uncleanness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And it shall come to pass in that day, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        of hosts, <i>that</i> I will cut off the names of the idols out of the land,
        and they shall no more be remembered: and also I will cause the prophets
        and the unclean spirit to pass out of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And it shall come to pass, <i>that</i> when any shall yet prophesy,
        then his father and his mother that begat him shall say unto him, Thou shalt
        not live; for thou speakest lies in the name of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>:
        and his father and his mother that begat him shall thrust him through when
        he prophesieth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And it shall come to pass in that day, <i>that</i> the prophets shall
        be ashamed every one of his vision, when he hath prophesied; neither shall
        they wear a rough garment to deceive: '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'but he shall say, I <i>am</i> no prophet, I <i>am</i> an husbandman;
        for man taught me to keep cattle from my youth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And <i>one</i> shall say unto him, What <i>are</i> these wounds in
        thine hands? Then he shall answer, <i>Those</i> with which I was wounded
        <i>in</i> the house of my friends.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Awake, O sword, against my shepherd, and against the man <i>that
        is</i> my fellow, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts: smite the
        shepherd, and the sheep shall be scattered: and I will turn mine hand upon
        the little ones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And it shall come to pass, <i>that</i> in all the land, saith the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, two parts therein shall be cut off <i>and</i>
        die; but the third shall be left therein. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And I will bring the third part through the fire, and will refine
        them as silver is refined, and will try them as gold is tried: they shall
        call on my name, and I will hear them: I will say, It <i>is</i> my people:
        and they shall say, The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>  <i>is</i> my God.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The City Saved'
      title: The City Saved
      number: 1
      content: '  Behold, the day of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> cometh, and
        thy spoil shall be divided in the midst of thee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For I will gather all nations against Jerusalem to battle; and the
        city shall be taken, and the houses rifled, and the women ravished; and half
        of the city shall go forth into captivity, and the residue of the people
        shall not be cut off from the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then shall the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> go forth, and fight against
        those nations, as when he fought in the day of battle.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And his feet shall stand in that day upon the mount of Olives, which
        <i>is</i> before Jerusalem on the east, and the mount of Olives shall cleave
        in the midst thereof toward the east and toward the west, <i>and there shall
        be</i> a very great valley; and half of the mountain shall remove toward
        the north, and half of it toward the south. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And ye shall flee <i>to</i> the valley of the mountains; for the
        valley of the mountains shall reach unto Azal: yea, ye shall flee, like as
        ye fled from before the earthquake in the days of Uzziah king of Judah: and
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> my God shall come, <i>and</i> all the saints
        with thee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And it shall come to pass in that day, <i>that</i> the light shall
        not be clear, <i>nor</i> dark: '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'but it shall be one day which shall be known to the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        not day, nor night: but it shall come to pass, <i>that</i> at evening time
        it shall be light. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Lord of All'
      title: Lord of All
      number: 8
      content: 'And it shall be in that day, <i>that</i> living waters shall go out
        from Jerusalem; half of them toward the former sea, and half of them toward
        the hinder sea: in summer and in winter shall it be.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> shall be king over all the earth:
        in that day shall there be one <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and his name
        one. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'All the land shall be turned as a plain from Geba to Rimmon south
        of Jerusalem: and it shall be lifted up, and inhabited in her place, from
        Benjamin''s gate unto the place of the first gate, unto the corner gate,
        and <i>from</i> the tower of Hananeel unto the king''s winepresses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And <i>men</i> shall dwell in it, and there shall be no more utter
        destruction; but Jerusalem shall be safely inhabited.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And this shall be the plague wherewith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        will smite all the people that have fought against Jerusalem; Their flesh
        shall consume away while they stand upon their feet, and their eyes shall
        consume away in their holes, and their tongue shall consume away in their
        mouth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And it shall come to pass in that day, <i>that</i> a great tumult
        from the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> shall be among them; and they shall
        lay hold every one on the hand of his neighbour, and his hand shall rise
        up against the hand of his neighbour. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Judah also shall fight at Jerusalem; and the wealth of all the
        heathen round about shall be gathered together, gold, and silver, and apparel,
        in great abundance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Universal Worship'
      title: Universal Worship
      number: 15
      content: 'And so shall be the plague of the horse, of the mule, of the camel,
        and of the ass, and of all the beasts that shall be in these tents, as this
        plague.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And it shall come to pass, <i>that</i> every one that is left of
        all the nations which came against Jerusalem shall even go up from year to
        year to worship the King, the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts, and to
        keep the feast of tabernacles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And it shall be, <i>that</i> whoso will not come up of <i>all</i>
        the families of the earth unto Jerusalem to worship the King, the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        of hosts, even upon them shall be no rain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And if the family of Egypt go not up, and come not, that <i>have</i>
        no <i>rain</i>; there shall be the plague, wherewith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        will smite the heathen that come not up to keep the feast of tabernacles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: An Age of Holiness'
      title: An Age of Holiness
      number: 19
      content: 'This shall be the punishment of Egypt, and the punishment of all
        nations that come not up to keep the feast of tabernacles.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'In that day shall there be upon the bells of the horses, HOLINESS
        UNTO THE <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>; and the pots
        in the <smallcaps><span class="ChapterContent_content__RrUqA">LORD</span></smallcaps>LORD''s
        house shall be like the bowls before the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Yea, every pot in Jerusalem and in Judah shall be holiness unto the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts: and all they that sacrifice shall come
        and take of them, and seethe therein: and in that day there shall be no more
        the Canaanite in the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts.'
      comments: []
